Sincerely yours,
BILLIEEILISHTOURS

We are so grateful for all of you. For Billie. This album. This era. Your support and everything that revolves around our platform. We really try to work as hard as possible to make this experience the best it can be for you. No matter how many sleepless nights it takes.

From music videos, interviews, tour, and some much more, you’ve brought together a community full of love and excitement to experience all that you’ve given to us.

We know we barely ever share any personal moments on here with you, but we really mean it when we say this.

You've made our 'job' here so fun and exciting and updating on this last year has been nothing but a thrill. It has been fantastic for us to watch the album grow since the very beginning and enjoy its release with all of you.

But somehow, everything worked out better than we could have ever imagined. 

We really want to take a moment to thank everyone who's made this past year so incredibly special.

Dear Happier Than Ever,

Where do we even begin? To say this was a whirlwind of a year would be an understatement. We started this past year thinking we probably wouldn't be able to update on tour or even go forward with many things we had planned. ? https://t.co/E7Rhq1qk2o

We're sending everyone lots of love! Stay safe, keep hydrated, be kind. And don't forget to have fun at these shows going forward.?
If you have any questions, our DMs are always open! ?

We also would like to apologize for not realizing this earlier & not putting it into action during other shows this tour. Our first priority is that you guys are safe. We're trying to filter our content & give you the updates that you need.

Last but not least, if you choose to be actively updating on tour please understand your responsibility of keeping fans safe. We understand posting information is exciting however not everything needs to be shared. Please continue to be kind and take care of each other. ?

Your actions are reflected on the show itself, The way we handle ourselves at venues can be badly reflected on not only the tour but Billie herself. Let’s do our part in ensuring we are kind and understanding to all venue staff unless they give you a reason not to be. ??
In addition to this, venues are not required to honour fan made queueing systems. Although it is appreciated when they do so, they are not to blame when these systems do not go as planned.

Furthermore, if you choose to queue early, it's within your own responsibility to abide by the venue protocols and regulations. 

This includes ensuring all rubbish, camping equipment and food is correctly disposed of prior to the show. Please do not litter or leave your trash!

If you choose to stay over night or go early, please make sure everyone in line is okay with you posting about it. Not everyone is comfortable with such information being shared. Especially if it puts other individuals at risk & venue staff is not available to ensure your safety.

This is to ensure the safety of those choosing to queue earlier than allowed. Providing public information as to where fans are queuing overnight in dark and unsafe conditions can be dangerous. We don't know who has access to this type of information & we want you to stay safe.

Hey guys! We wanted to talk to you about queuing and camping for shows a little bit. You might have noticed a few changes regarding our updates on queues. We have decided to not post queue updates until the day of the shows. ?

Please plan extra time to bring it back to your cars, hotels or just the bin. There's plenty of time and if you ask someone to hold your space, we're sure you won't lose your spot. It takes little to no time to do so and it would help everyone around you immensely.

However that does not mean you can just leave it on the ground once you're ready to go inside. It's disrespectful towards the staff that has to clean it up and it's also not what the narrative of this tour is. In fact, it's the exact opposite.

And we don't just mean after the show but after you have finished queuing. We understand that it's cold and that it's a long wait which is why you might be in the needs of blankets, food, water, umbrellas etc.

Hey everyone! We just wanted to make a post on something that's been brought to our attention several times now. Normally, this should go without saying but if you are camping outside or queuing early, please pick up your trash and other things that may remain afterwards.
